  "text": "Graph Traversal. Figure 3 illustrates a frontier-based graph traversal algorithm; such algorithms have been shown to execute efficiently on GPUs [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . The kernel is given three arguments in global memory: a graph structure, and two arrays of graph nodes. Initially, n0 contains the starting nodes to process. Private variable level records the current frontier level, and in_nodes and out_nodes point to distinct arrays recording the nodes to be processed during the current and next frontier, respectively.",
